The official 2005 ASP World Tour video, featuring Kelly Slater's road to his seventh world title, book-ending a career as both the youngest and olderst surfer to wear the mantle of World Champion.
How good can pro surfing get? Well, you're about to find out. The ASP and Surfing Magazine bring you the 2005 Dream Tour DVD. The 2005 Fosters ASP Men's World Championship Tour will go down as the greatest season in pro surfing history. Follow the entire 11-stop 2005 WCT as it snakes its way through prime surfing hotspots like Snapper, Teahupo'o, Cloudbreak, J-Bay and Pipeline.Cheer on Mick Fanning's comeback win at his home break of Snapper Rocks, Scratch your head in disbelief as Kelly Slater rewrites the record books at Teahupo'o, Hang on and pray as "The Perfect Storm hits Fiji, Bite your nails as Andy Irons heats up the world title race with epic wins in Japan and France, Be there on the beach in Brazil as Kelly claims World Title number seven, And take a seat on the beach at Pipeline as the tour reaches an epic and emitonal climax.
